# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Sovereign Agent Lab — Environment Variables
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE
# ────────────────────
# 1. Copy this file:   cp .env.example .env
# 2. Open .env and replace every placeholder with your real key.
# 3. Never commit .env — it is in .gitignore for a reason.
#
# RULES FOR ALL KEYS
# ──────────────────
# • No quotes around values:    NEBIUS_KEY=sk-abc123     ✓
#                               NEBIUS_KEY="sk-abc123"   ✗
# • No spaces around the =:     NEBIUS_KEY=sk-abc123     ✓
#                               NEBIUS_KEY = sk-abc123   ✗
# • If a key is not needed yet, leave the placeholder — don't delete the line.
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WEEK 1 and beyond — Required from day one
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Nebius Token Factory — your primary LLM API key.
# Used for every model call throughout the course:
#   - Qwen3-32B          (default for the research agent and Rasa CALM LLM)
#   - Llama-3.3-70B      (Exercise 1 main model — Base variant, not _fast)
#   - Gemma-2-2b-it      (Exercise 1 small model for the stress test)
#   - Qwen3-Embedding-8B (Rasa CALM flow retrieval)
# Get yours at: https://studio.nebius.ai → API Keys
NEBIUS_KEY=sk-your-key-here

# Optional — override the default research agent model.
# Leave unset to use the scaffold default (Qwen/Qwen3-32B).
# Good alternatives that also emit correct tool_calls on Nebius:
#   nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b
#   Qwen/Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B-Thinking
# Do NOT use meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct for the research agent — it
# does not reliably emit native tool_calls on the Nebius endpoint.
# Do NOT use any model suffixed `_fast` — those were deprecated 2026-04-13.
# RESEARCH_MODEL=Qwen/Qwen3-32B

# Optional — wire in a live image generation provider for Exercise 2 Task B.
# Leave unset to use the deterministic placehold.co fallback (default).
# See sovereign_agent/tools/venue_tools.py → generate_event_flyer for the
# contract. Any OpenAI-compatible images.generate endpoint will work.
# FLYER_IMAGE_MODEL=
# FLYER_IMAGE_BASE_URL=

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WEEK 1 — Exercise 3: Rasa Pro CALM (required for Exercise 3 and PyNanoClaw's structured half)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Rasa Pro Developer Edition — free licence, up to 1,000 conversations/month.
#
# HOW TO GET IT (takes about 2 minutes):
#   1. Go to: https://rasa.com/rasa-pro-developer-edition-license-key-request
#   2. Enter your email address and accept the licence terms.
#   3. Rasa will email you a licence key — check your inbox (and spam folder).
#   4. Paste the key below. It looks like a long string, not like an API key.
#
# The Developer Edition is free and lets you run Rasa Pro with CALM locally.
# No credit card required.
RASA_PRO_LICENSE=your-rasa-pro-licence-key-here

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Final consolidated assignment (Weeks 3–5, releases 2026-04-18)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Tavily — web search API used by the research agent in Week 2.
# Free tier: 1,000 searches/month. Sign up at: https://tavily.com
# Leave blank if not yet on the Week 2 material.
TAVILY_API_KEY=tvly-your-key-here

# Pinecone — vector database for the RAG pipeline (memory layer).
# Free tier: 1 index, 100k vectors. Sign up at: https://pinecone.io
# Leave blank if not yet on the memory material.
PINECONE_API_KEY=pcsk-your-key-here
PINECONE_INDEX_NAME=sovereign-agent

# LangSmith — tracing and observability for LangGraph agents.
# Free tier available. Sign up at: https://smith.langchain.com
# Leave blank if not yet on the observability material.
LANGSMITH_API_KEY=lsv2-your-key-here
LANGSMITH_PROJECT=sovereign-agent-lab
# Set to "true" to enable tracing, "false" to disable.
LANGCHAIN_TRACING_V2=false

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL — Voice pipeline (final assignment, optional component)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Speechmatics — speech-to-text (ASR) and text-to-speech (TTS).
# Used in the optional voice pipeline: microphone → Speechmatics → Rasa
# → Speechmatics → speaker. The voice pipeline is an OPTIONAL extension
# in the final PyNanoClaw assignment — the core system works without it.
# Sign up at: https://speechmatics.com → API Access
# Leave blank if you are not building the voice pipeline.
SPEECHMATICS_API_KEY=your-speechmatics-key-here
